How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Kirby Nguyen
5.0 out of 5 stars Gently adjust needle length & read instructions about adjusting needle length before using
Reviewed in the United States on April 7, 2023
Verified Purchase
This is an excellent at-home tool, and Dr. Pen really wants its customers to have a positive experience with its products. If you are already well into your skincare journey and routine, then adding this microneedling stamp will help your skin reach a new level of appearance. It's really affordable and great if you are not quite ready/sure about getting more intense treatments from a doctor for example.

When I broke my first stamp, I contacted their customer service email to ask for a replacement, and they sent me an additional stamp. They also clarified how to adjust the needles setting the next time.

Make sure you sanitize your skin and the tool as much as to can when you use it because no matter what tool you use lack of cleanliness with definitely negatively affect your experience.

I would also say proceed slowly and carefully. Don't just go "stamp happy" all over your face because that might cause more damage to your skin. I would also clean the needles with alcohol between each application.

Microneedle stamps are definitely more effective than derma rollers because they offer more control and produce less abrasion. That's why I switched from a roller to this stamp. Rollers always made me nervous even when I was really slow and deliberate in my technique.

I experience near instant results after each use. It works as intended. My skin just drinks up the toner and moisturizer I apply afterwards. My acne scars become less visible, less red/purple. I also have this scowl-wrinkle line between my eyebrows that has been getting deeper over the last year, and after each session, the wrinkle has gotten less and less visible.

Samantha Lucas
4.0 out of 5 stars Great Buy!!
Reviewed in the United States on March 28, 2023
Verified Purchase
This stamp was a great buy for my first couple of microneedling with a skinbooster. I tried a dermaroller but felt like I was losing a lot of product being able to roll at .25 mm. This stamp is great for beginners. Each area of the face is a little thicker and the stamp gives you the option to adjust the needle depth. I have a Dr. PEN and still find myself reaching for this stamp if or when I run out of cartridges. However, I was very unhappy with my last Dr. STAMP.I could not get the needles to move up or down by twisting the handle. I ended up breaking the handle. I honestly have had it for a 6 months but it was to late to return it. If you do purchase this check to make sure it actually moves properly before forgetting about it!!

3.0 out of 5 stars It works well but just one complaint
Reviewed in the United States on May 24, 2023
Verified Purchase
Everything works great about this, other than difficulty cleaning the needles of blood and anything on them after use. I soak it in alcohol and hydrogen peroxide and still see some remaining debris or blood stain.
Beside that my main complaint is that when I dialed it back down to 0, one time the needles would come back through the holes while trying to adjust it to come up. It was offset or stuck and wouldn’t align with holes. I had to carefully remove the cover over the needles and then adjust needle high all the way up and carefully install cover back down into place. It happens again after trying to set it back to zero. So now I just leave them sticking a little out but be protected from the cap.

That was my biggest complaint of the product, it’s great but hopefully if you have that issue you can do a little quick fix like I did. But we shouldn’t have to do that.
